主要翻译
 
volatile adj figurative (situation: potentially violent)
           --> SC Simplified Chinese 容易失控的，危险的 róng yì shī kòng de ，wēi xiǎn de TC Traditional Chinese 危險的  (形势)
 -- The situation became more volatile when troops arrived.
 
volatile adj figurative (person: quick to anger)
           --> SC Simplified Chinese 容易激怒的，脾气暴躁的 róng yì jī nù de ，pí qì bào zào de  (人)
 -- You need to approach her carefully - she's very volatile.
 
volatile adj (chemistry: evaporating easily)
           --> SC Simplified Chinese 挥发性的，易挥发的 huī fā xìng de ，yì huī fā de  (化学)
 -- Gases from volatile compounds may be flammable.
 
volatile adj figurative (unstable)
           --> SC Simplified Chinese 不稳定的 bù wěn dìng de TC Traditional Chinese 不穩定的  
 "" 
           --> SC Simplified Chinese 剧烈波动的 
 -- My sister doesn't like investing in the stock market because it is volatile.

复合形式： 
 
nonvolatile, non-volatile adj (chemistry: not evaporating)
           --> SC Simplified Chinese 不挥发的，非挥发性的 bù huī fā de，fēi huī fā xìng de  (化学术语)
 
nonvolatile, non-volatile adj figurative (not changeable)
           --> SC Simplified Chinese 不易变的 bú yì biàn de TC Traditional Chinese 不易變的  
 "" 
           --> SC Simplified Chinese 不善变的 bú yì biàn de，bú shàn biàn de 
 
smelling salts, sal volatile npl (medicine: for faintness)
           --> SC Simplified Chinese 嗅盐  (苏醒剂)
 
volatile situation n (state of affairs liable to turn violent)
           --> SC Simplified Chinese 冲突一触即发的情况  
 "" 
           --> SC Simplified Chinese 随时可能爆发冲突的情况 

